ging them in the work presented throughout. The examples and visual aids will help them recognise all the details presented and represented in a photograph. For researchers who would like to try their hand at photovoice as a method or as a framework to foster a more participatory approach, this is the ultimate guide to kickstart their project.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aLorenz, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z9783111299655oZDB-23-BUPP40uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447369400?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447369400423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447369400/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2024